  "body": "I am running k8s 1.15 and I see kubectl top --help is returning the following info:\r\n...This command requires Heapster to be correctly configured and working on the server.\r\n\r\nAs far as I know Heaspter is deprecated since 1.11.\r\n\r\n1) Should the command help be updated i.e. replace Heapster with Metrics Server?\r\n\r\n2) Will the command work if Metrics Server is deployed in the cluster?\r\n\r\n3) Is kubectl top utility the easiest way to display (actual) resource usage info for pods and nodes? Any suggestions?\r\n",
